headline: COVID-19 RNA vaccines are safe, cannot modify human DNA; death rate in vaccinated people isn’t higher than in unvaccinated people
details: “The protein then can bind to your DNA and irreversibly change it”; “[It] has several different type of lipids on it that have never been injected into human beings before”; “We could be looking at right now as many as 12,000 deaths”

headline: Oxygen in the air doesn’t prevent people from getting tetanus through cuts with dirty or rusty objects; the vaccine is important to prevent infection
details: "The tetanus bacteria is an anaerobic bacteria. That means that it cannot live in the presence of oxygen. You cannot get tetanus by stepping on a rusty nail."

headline: Mask mandates are associated with reductions in the spread of COVID-19 cases and deaths; contrary to One America News article
details: “CDC: Face Masks Don’t Prevent COVID-19, Study Finds Masks Have Negligible Impact on Coronavirus Numbers,” CDC “admitted such mandates do not make any statistical difference.”

headline: Vaccines are safe and aren’t associated with autoimmune disease, contrary to claim in viral video by chiropractor Steven Baker
details: “Vaccines cause autoimmune disease”; COVID-19 vaccine will “change your genes”; aborted fetal tissue is in vaccines

headline: Data from Israel showed that the Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine reduces the likelihood of dying from COVID-19; analysis in a forum post claiming the opposite is flawed
details: “the Pfizer vaccines, for the elderly, killed during the 5-week vaccination period about 40 times more people than the disease itself would have killed”
source: Haim Yativ, Children’s Health Defense, GreenMedInfo

headline: COVID-19 vaccines start to provide protection within two weeks of the first dose, with no evidence they increase the risk of infection before then
details: “Now a Public Health England report confirms that infections increase during the fortnight after vaccination”

headline: Six residents in a German nursing home died from COVID-19, not from vaccines
details: “25% of residents in German nursing home died after Pfizer vaccine”; a team including a soldier in uniform used force to vaccinate residents

headline: The U.S. leads the world in number of COVID-19 vaccine doses administered, but not in the proportion of the population vaccinated
details: “In five weeks, America has administered the most COVID vaccine shots than any other country in the world.”

headline: Yes, COVID-19 vaccines will help us safely resume normal activities like going to restaurants and meeting people, once enough people are vaccinated for herd immunity
details: The COVID-19 vaccines won’t let us stop mask-wearing, physical distancing and restaurants, pubs, and cinemas still remain closed, so why vaccinate?
